  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "框架效應 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-framing-effect",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / decision / language / risk</p>\n    <h1>框架效應</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Framing Effect</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">同樣一組事實，只因為被包裝成收益、損失、成功率或失敗率，人就可能做出完全不同的決策。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『只是換個說法』和『其實已經改變你怎麼感受風險』拆開，因為很多決策偏移都不是證據變了，而是語言先塑形了。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>決策偏誤 / 表述影響</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Choices shift when equivalent information is presented differently</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>等價資訊、收益損失框架、風險感受、語言暗示</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在規格、簡報與風險溝通裡看見表述方式如何改變選擇</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>表述</span>\n      <span>感受</span>\n      <span>選擇</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>資訊沒有變，選擇卻變了，差別常只在你先被帶進哪個框裡</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">框架效應提醒你：人的選擇不只受內容影響，也受內容被放進哪種語意容器影響。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>表述總得選角度，但一旦某個角度特別凸顯損失或收益，原本應該等價的選項就可能被感受成完全不同。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先找等價是否真的等價</strong>\n        <p>如果只是文字包裝不同，卻得到不同反應，就可能是框架效應在作用。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再問哪種感受被放大</strong>\n        <p>是風險、損失、成功希望，還是道德感？</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後做雙框檢查</strong>\n        <p>重要決策最好同時用正向與負向表述看一次。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個其實沒變的選項，只因說法不同就換票開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">框架效應特別常出現在醫療、產品預設、風險簡報與管理溝通。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>把同一個方案說成『90% 成功率』和『10% 失敗率』，即使數學等價，接受度仍可能顯著不同。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>人不是只在算機率，也在感受語言幫自己點亮了哪一種心理場景。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">同一資訊換不同表述</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">情緒與風險感受被改寫</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">原本等價的選項得到不同偏好</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>框架效應最有力的提醒是：溝通方式本身，就是決策介面的組成部分。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看表述偏移的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">不是所有 framing 都是不誠實操控，但重要選擇至少該知道自己被哪種語氣推了一把。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>收益或損失</strong>\n        <p>同一方案是被說成保住多少，還是會失去多少？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>絕對值或比例</strong>\n        <p>小基數的大比例和大基數的小比例，感覺很不一樣。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>責任語氣</strong>\n        <p>這是被描述成主動作為，還是被描述成避免犯錯？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>時間視角</strong>\n        <p>強調短期痛感或長期回報，也會改變風險接受度。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>表述方式</th>\n            <th>感受被推向哪裡</th>\n            <th>選擇可能如何偏</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>成功率</td>\n            <td>樂觀與保住收益</td>\n            <td>較願意接受方案</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>失敗率</td>\n            <td>損失與風險顯化</td>\n            <td>較容易保守或拒絕</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>節省成本</td>\n            <td>看見效率收益</td>\n            <td>較願意支持變更</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼換句話說真的會換掉決策</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為人不是只回應事實，也會回應事實被放進的情境感與情緒方向。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>語言會先定義情緒入口</strong>\n        <p>先看見損失還是先看見收益，會改變整個評估姿態。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>等價不等於等感</strong>\n        <p>數學對等不會自動轉成心理對等。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>表述像隱形預設</strong>\n        <p>它不需要改變資料，就能改變你第一眼把重心放在哪。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">框架效應不是說語言比事實重要，而是說語言會決定你怎麼靠近事實。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把雙框檢查帶回規格、簡報與產品文案</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對產品、工程和管理來說，框架效應最常讓團隊在以為自己很理性時，其實被文案順手帶偏。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>風險簡報</strong>\n        <p>把 rollback 成本講成延誤，和講成避免事故，會導向不同決策氛圍。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>產品選項</strong>\n        <p>訂閱方案若以省下多少表述，和以會損失什麼表述，轉換率常不同。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>專案提案</strong>\n        <p>講變更的好處與講不變的代價，對管理層接受度的影響可能完全不同。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>重要決策請至少做一次雙向 framing，把同一方案用收益與損失各講一遍。</li>\n      <li>若某提案只有靠單一框架才看起來合理，通常就值得再多檢查。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">框架效應不是說所有說法都在操控，而是說表述本來就會塑形。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要資料正確就不受 framing 影響</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>同資料仍可能因表述方式而改變選擇。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>所以不能用任何有角度的語言</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不可能完全無框架，重點是要自覺並做對照。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只有行銷才會用 framing</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>醫療、法規、工程提案與事故溝通都很常見。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>如果我把同一件事換另一種說法，這個決定還成立嗎</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在高影響溝通前。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>這個選項若改成相反框架表述，我還會一樣偏好嗎</strong>\n        <p>能幫你看見選擇是否過度依賴語言包裝。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>我現在的文案是在幫人看清事實，還是在偷偷指定感受方向</strong>\n        <p>兩者有時會混在一起。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 prospect theory、risk communication 與 choice architecture。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 framing effect 為主，再把它帶回風險溝通、產品文案與管理提案。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Framing effect 條目整理了等價資訊如何因表述不同而改變決策。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Framing_effect_(psychology)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Framing Effect</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>理論背景</strong>\n        <p>Prospect theory 可作為對照，理解收益與損失框架為何影響風險偏好。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prospect_theory\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Prospect Theory</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰應用</strong>\n        <p>Choice architecture 條目有助於把這個偏誤帶回實際設計與政策場景。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choice_architecture\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Choice Architecture</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你正在寫的提案，用相反框架重寫一次，看結論是否還站得住。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
